algorithms.shortestPaths

Class FloydWarshalAllPairs

  • java.lang.Object
    • algorithms.shortestPaths.FloydWarshalAllPairs

  • public class FloydWarshalAllPairs
extends java.lang.Object
    from Cormen et al. "Intro to Algorithms" finds shortest paths between all pairs of vertices in a directed graph with dynamic programming. The runtime complexity is O(V^3). W, D W is an nxn matrix of w[i][j] where each entry is the edge weight if any between i and j. has values 0 if i==j and inf where there is no connection. D is an nxn matrix of d[i][j] where each entry is the weight of the shortest path between i and j. d[i][j]_k = w[i][j] if k = 0 = min( d[i][k]_(k-1) + d[k][j]_(k-1) ) if k >= 1
    Author:
    nichole
